        "page": "313-325",
        "title": "Numbers as functions",
        "type": "article-journal",
        "volume": "5",
        "issue": "4",
        "ISSN": "2070-0474",
        "URL": "https://doi.org/10.1134/S2070046613040055",
        "abstract": "In this survey I discuss A. Buium’s theory of “differential equations in the p-adic direction” ([8]) and its interrelations with “geometry over the field 𝔽₁”, on the background of various approaches to p-adic models in theoretical physics (cf. [1, 30])."
